<style>
  .tc-wrap {
    background: #000;
    color: #fff;
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
  }

  /* ── Hero ── */
  .tc-hero {
    padding: 96px 60px 80px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
    max-width: 900px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) { .tc-hero { padding: 64px 24px 56px; } }

  .tc-eyebrow {
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.3em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.35);
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .tc-headline {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 900;
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 7rem);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    line-height: 0.93;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    color: #fff;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }

  .tc-sub {
    font-family: 'Barlow', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.62);
    max-width: 560px;
  }

  /* ── Article body ── */
  .tc-article {
    padding: 80px 60px;
    max-width: 780px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) { .tc-article { padding: 56px 24px; } }

  .tc-article h2 {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 900;
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.6rem);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    color: #fff;
    margin: 56px 0 20px;
    padding-top: 40px;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
  }
  .tc-article h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; padding-top: 0; border-top: none; }

  .tc-article p {
    font-family: 'Barlow', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.72);
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .tc-article strong {
    color: #fff;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .tc-article ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0 0 24px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 12px;
  }

  .tc-article ul li {
    font-family: 'Barlow', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.72);
    padding-left: 22px;
    position: relative;
  }

  .tc-article ul li::before {
    content: '—';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.25);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  /* Highlight rule — stands out from body copy */
  .tc-rule {
    border-left: 2px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.25);
    padding: 16px 20px;
    margin: 28px 0;
    font-family: 'Barlow', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.78);
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
  }
  .tc-rule strong { color: #fff; }

  /* ── Coming Soon callout ── */
  .tc-coming-soon {
    background: #fff;
    color: #000;
    padding: 80px 60px;
    margin-top: 0;
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) { .tc-coming-soon { padding: 56px 24px; } }

  .tc-coming-soon__eyebrow {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.3em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .tc-coming-soon__heading {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 900;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.8rem);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    line-height: 0.95;
    color: #000;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    max-width: 600px;
  }

  .tc-coming-soon__body {
    font-family: 'Barlow', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: rgba(0,0,0,0.65);
    max-width: 520px;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }

  .tc-coming-soon__form {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0;
    max-width: 480px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .tc-coming-soon__form { flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; }
  }

  .tc-coming-soon__input {
    flex: 1;
    padding: 14px 18px;
    border: 1.5px solid #000;
    border-right: none;
    background: #fff;
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: #000;
    outline: none;
    border-radius: 0;
    appearance: none;
  }
  .tc-coming-soon__input::placeholder { color: rgba(0,0,0,0.35); }
  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .tc-coming-soon__input { border-right: 1.5px solid #000; }
  }

  .tc-coming-soon__btn {
    padding: 14px 28px;
    background: #000;
    color: #fff;
    border: 1.5px solid #000;
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    cursor: pointer;
    border-radius: 0;
    transition: background 200ms, color 200ms;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .tc-coming-soon__btn:hover { background: #222; }

  .tc-coming-soon__success {
    display: none;
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: #000;
    margin-top: 14px;
  }
</style>

<div class="tc-wrap">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <div class="tc-hero">
    <p class="tc-eyebrow">Polaris Car Care — Care Guide</p>
    <h1 class="tc-headline">How To Clean<br>Your Microfiber<br>Towels.</h1>
    <p class="tc-sub">Most people ruin their microfibers in the wash. Here's how to not do that.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Article Body -->
  <div class="tc-article">

    <h2>Why Microfiber Is Different</h2>
    <p>Microfiber works by trapping contamination inside millions of tiny split loops. A single towel can hold 8x its weight in water. That performance depends entirely on those loops staying open and uncoated.</p>
    <p>The wrong wash routine doesn't just clean less effectively — it permanently degrades the fiber structure. <strong>Fabric softener is the biggest offender.</strong> It coats the fibers in a waxy film that prevents them from absorbing anything. One wash with softener and the towel is functionally dead.</p>
    <p>Cotton lint from washing with regular towels or clothes is second. It embeds into the loops and kills absorption.</p>

    <h2>The Right Way To Wash</h2>
    <p><strong>Shake the towel out first.</strong> Knock off loose dirt before it goes into the machine.</p>
    <p><strong>Wash alone or with other microfiber only.</strong> Never with cotton, denim, or anything that sheds lint.</p>
    <p><strong>Cold or warm water only.</strong> Hot water shrinks and damages the polyester/polyamide split fibers. 30°C / 90°F max.</p>
    <p><strong>Use a free and clear detergent.</strong> No dyes, no fragrance, no fabric softener built in. All Free &amp; Clear works. So does Seventh Generation. A small amount of Dawn dish soap in a pinch — strong surfactant, rinses clean, just use a little.</p>
    <div class="tc-rule"><strong>No fabric softener. Ever.</strong> Not in the wash. Not in the dryer. No dryer sheets either.</div>
    <p><strong>Add ¼ cup white vinegar to the wash.</strong> Not as a cleaner — as a rinse aid. It strips mineral buildup from hard water and keeps fibers soft without clogging them.</p>
    <p><strong>Low heat or air dry.</strong> High heat degrades the fiber split. Air dry when possible. If you use the dryer, no heat or low heat only.</p>

    <h2>For Heavily Contaminated Towels</h2>
    <p>Wash polish and wax towels separately from drying towels. Product contamination transfers and is hard to fully flush out.</p>
    <p>If a towel has a heavy wax or sealant load, a hot bucket soak (around 60°C / 140°F) with a few drops of dish soap before washing will help break down the oils before the machine cycle.</p>

    <h2>What To Stop Doing</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Washing with regular laundry</li>
      <li>Any fabric softener or dryer sheet</li>
      <li>Hot water or high heat drying</li>
      <li>Storing contaminated towels with clean ones</li>
      <li>Using the same towel for everything — paint, glass, interior, and drying all need separate towels</li>
    </ul>

  </div>

</div>

<!-- Coming Soon: Polaris Microfiber Wash -->
<div class="tc-coming-soon">
  <p class="tc-coming-soon__eyebrow">Coming Soon</p>
  <h2 class="tc-coming-soon__heading">Polaris Microfiber Wash</h2>
  <p class="tc-coming-soon__body">We built a detergent specifically for microfiber. No fillers. No fragrance. Formulated to strip wax, sealant, and product contamination without touching the fiber structure. Join the list to get early access.</p>

  {% form 'customer', id: 'tc-notify-form' %}
    <input type="hidden" name="contact[tags]" value="microfiber-wash-waitlist">
    <div class="tc-coming-soon__form">
      <input
        type="email"
        name="contact[email]"
        class="tc-coming-soon__input"
        placeholder="your@email.com"
        required
        autocomplete="email"
      >
      <button type="submit" class="tc-coming-soon__btn">Notify Me</button>
    </div>
    <p class="tc-coming-soon__success" id="tc-notify-success">You're on the list. We'll reach out when it's ready.</p>
  {% endform %}
</div>

<script>
  (function () {
    var form = document.getElementById('tc-notify-form');
    if (!form) return;
    form.addEventListener('submit', function () {
      setTimeout(function () {
        var success = document.getElementById('tc-notify-success');
        if (success) success.style.display = 'block';
        var btn = form.querySelector('.tc-coming-soon__btn');
        if (btn) { btn.disabled = true; btn.textContent = 'Done'; }
      }, 400);
    });
  })();
</script>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Towel Care Guide",
  "settings": [],
  "presets": [
    { "name": "Towel Care Guide" }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
